Go to the documentation of this file.00001 /*
00002  *  TinyIRReceiver.hpp
00003  *
00004  *  Receives IR protocol data of NEC protocol using pin change interrupts.
00005  *  NEC is the protocol of most cheap remote controls for Arduino.
00006  *
00007  *  No parity check is done!
00008  *  On a completely received IR command, the user function handleReceivedIRData(uint16_t aAddress, uint8_t aCommand, bool isRepetition)
00009  *  is called in Interrupt context but with interrupts being enabled to enable use of delay() etc.
00010  *  !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
00011  *  Functions called in interrupt context should be running as short as possible,
00012  *  so if you require longer action, save the data (address + command) and handle them in the main loop.
00013  *  !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
00014  *
00015  *
00016  *  Copyright (C) 2021  Armin Joachimsmeyer
00017  *  armin.joachimsmeyer@gmail.com
00018  *
00019  *  This file is part of IRMP https://github.com/ukw100/IRMP.
00020  *  This file is part of Arduino-IRremote https://github.com/Arduino-IRremote/Arduino-IRremote.
